As an introverted, privacy-conscious self-employed creative individual, running a business shouldn't feel this awkward, but sometimes it does. Most online resources and mentors tell you to interact with large (evil) tech companies in an extroverted way. Here, advertise, follow the algorithm, share your personal charm. Get verified on that platform, be available 24/7, answer questions with your own videos, and respond immediately. Video, video, and video again.
1/3
This year is my year of transformation for me.
I don't want to continue giving my money, data, and energy to large tech companies, nor do I want to listen to mentors who only offer a single extroverted solution for everyone. I'm exploring new business models while also trying to overcome my long-held belief that success can only be achieved by following a specific way of doing things.
Wish me luck!
The first step has already been taken.
I've left FB, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and unsubscribed from my personal WhatsApp account.
Yesterday, I also removed the last external tracker from my website - Google Analytics, and it felt amazing.
To better support GDPR, I recently subscribed to a European CRM service and will be migrating my business over the next few weeks.
I've transferred my MX records to Proton, now I have full SPF, DKIM, and DMARC, without having to pay Google for basic email verification.
3/3
